comment:
Aquaman is a really good film and shows what route DC should have taken to get to Justice League.

They tried to rush to the team-up film to establish themselves as a rival to Marvel. Never ever should've done that. Even the Snyder version of Justice League still isn't particularly good. It's better, but the characters are still underdeveloped (particularly Aquaman) 

Superman needed to stay dead a little longer as well. Put Aquaman and Shazam after BvS, then do Justice League followed by the WW sequel, Cyborg, and Flash films. (That was the route they should've taken)

The biggest wrench was Suicide Squad. They wanted a Guardians of the Galaxy rival and made that instead of making this or Shazam earlier.
